      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JACQUELINE ROSE NZ (1) was held up when finishing 8.5 metres away here last week so could have finished closer. Came from this barrier for fourth at Menangle prior so is worth another chance. LACHIES IDEAL (4) has been coming from the back row in higher-graded races of late but scored back-to-back Tamworth wins from this line earlier in the campaign so looks well served here. LADY DELORIS (2) wasn't disgraced when she came from wider in her latest outing at Penrith. Draws well and she could enjoy the return to a circuit and distance where she has placed in four of her five attempts. LETSGETROWDY (6) is an interesting newcomer to the Darren Elder yard from SA where he put together a string of placings earlier in his campaign. Could measure up.",
